  "prompt": "How do I book a round trip on Uber such that it is counted as a single ride?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Uber does not officially offer a feature to book a round trip as a single ride within the app. However, users can use a few workarounds to achieve a similar effect:\n\n1. **Schedule Two Rides:** You can book your first ride to your destination and then schedule a return trip for later. While this counts as two separate rides, it allows you to plan your journey in advance.\n\n2. **Use Uber's Multi-Stop Feature:** If you're making a trip with multiple stops (but not necessarily a round trip), you can use the multi-stop feature. This allows you to add a stop on the way to your destination and then return directly from there. However, this will not count as a single ride but may help in planning your time.\n\n3. **Contact Uber Support:** If you're looking for a specific feature or have a unique situation in mind, you can reach out to Uber support through the app. They may be able to provide guidance or let you know if any new features have been added since my last update.\n\n4. **Third-Party Services:** Some third-party apps and services allow you to book rides in a way that might provide you with a round-trip option, but this typically involves using Uber's API and might not be as straightforward as using the Uber app directly.\n\nAlways check the latest version of the Uber app or their website for any new features that may have been introduced since my last update.",
